reviews.text:
Visited this cafe during the weekday lunch peak.  The restaurant was extremely busy, and there were only two service crew on duty.  Thankfully, the self-ordering system made placing my order a breeze, and the food arrived quickly.

I opted for the most expensive set lunch, Nasi Lemak with fried Turmeric Chicken Leg with a side salad and hot coffee. The total cost came to $22.66, inclusive of tax and service charge.  Unfortunately, the food was mediocre, and the chicken leg was quite dry.  The portion size was also rather small for the price. The coffee was passable though.

However, I must commend the 2 service crew, who managed everything so efficiently despite the rush. I might return only if I need a quick lunch in the area.

Pretty average food at restaurant prices. Toast was nice. My fav chic hor fun still nice but kway tiao a bbit soggy. Prawn mee has a nice spice to it - can use real fresh prawns instead of crystal prawns? Since this is a prawn mee.

Tea time! Tried the toast with condensed milk. Buttered bread was toasted just nice with generous condensed milk spread over. Would prefer the toast without the crust but well…that’s personal preference. Washed that all down with hot soya milk. Wife ate the spicy prawn noodle and no complaints from her.

Scan QR, place order & pay online. Not ideal for persons who struggle with digital ordering & payments.
$3.40 for a small cup of white coffee, $4.20? For 2 slices of kaya toast
Friendly staff!!

Always enjoy the meatless noodles especially the curry noodles.  Price is reasonable before taxes.

Good service at this Square 2 outlet.
